    public class WorkItemExecutorImpl
extends ThreadPoolExecutor
implements WorkItemExecutor
    An implementation of WorkItemExecutor that provides methods to manage the threads executing the work item.

        public WorkItemExecutorImpl(int corePoolSize)
        Creates a new WorkItemExecutorImpl with the given initial parameters and default thread factory and rejected execution handler.
        Parameters:
        corePoolSize - the number of threads to keep in the pool, even if they are idle, unless allowCoreThreadTimeOut is set
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if one of the following holds:
        corePoolSize < 0
        keepAliveTime < 0
        maximumPoolSize <= 0
        maximumPoolSize < corePoolSize
        NullPointerException - if workQueue is null

      • WorkItemExecutorImpl

        public WorkItemExecutorImpl(int corePoolSize,
                            int maximumPoolSize,
                            long keepAliveTime,
                            TimeUnit unit,
                            BlockingQueue<Runnable> workQueue)
        Creates a new WorkItemExecutorImpl with the given initial parameters and default thread factory and rejected execution handler.
        Parameters:
        corePoolSize - the number of threads to keep in the pool, even if they are idle, unless allowCoreThreadTimeOut is set
        maximumPoolSize - the maximum number of threads to allow in the pool
        keepAliveTime - when the number of threads is greater than the core, this is the maximum time that excess idle threads will wait for new tasks before terminating.
        unit - the time unit for the keepAliveTime argument
        workQueue - the queue to use for holding tasks before they are executed. This queue will hold only the Runnable tasks submitted by the execute method.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if one of the following holds:
        corePoolSize < 0
        keepAliveTime < 0
        maximumPoolSize <= 0
        maximumPoolSize < corePoolSize
        NullPointerException - if workQueue is null
